<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>West Virginia Set to Host NCAA Super Regionals</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/2/baseball-west-virginia-set-to-host-ncaa-super-regionals</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/2/baseball-west-virginia-set-to-host-ncaa-super-regionals</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="WVU baseball players sing Country Roads after winning the NCAA Morgantown Regional." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/2/WVU_V_UK_Monday-127.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University baseball team will host the NCAA Super Regionals against Cal Poly from June 5-7. First pitch on Friday and Saturday is scheduled for 12 p.m. on both days with Sunday's game time to be determined. It is a best-of-three format with Sunday's game only being played if needed.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/WVU_V_UK_Monday-127.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/WVU_V_UK_Monday-127.jpg"><media:title>WVU baseball players sing Country Roads after winning the NCAA Morgantown Regional.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/WVU_V_UK_Monday-127.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 2 Jun 2026 12:55:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59159</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Claims Morgantown Regional Title</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/2/baseball-west-virginia-claims-morgantown-regional-title</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/2/baseball-west-virginia-claims-morgantown-regional-title</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="The West Virginia baseball team poses for a photo after winning the Morgantown Regional" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/2/060126_BSB_Kentucky_NCAAT_GB-11.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – For the third consecutive season, the West Virginia University baseball team advanced to the NCAA Super Regionals as the Mountaineers defeated Kentucky, 6-5, in 10 innings, Monday evening at Kendrick Family Ballpark to win the Morgantown Regional.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/060126_BSB_Kentucky_NCAAT_GB-11.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/060126_BSB_Kentucky_NCAAT_GB-11.jpg"><media:title>The West Virginia baseball team poses for a photo after winning the Morgantown Regional</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/060126_BSB_Kentucky_NCAAT_GB-11.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 2 Jun 2026 00:49:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59156</s:story_id></item><item><title>NCAA Super Regional Parking and Tailgating Information</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/3/baseball-ncaa-super-regional-parking-and-tailgating-information</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/3/baseball-ncaa-super-regional-parking-and-tailgating-information</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tailgating at Kendrick Family Ballpark" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/3/WVU_V_UK_Monday-12.jpeg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Due to heavy traffic expected in and around Kendrick Family Ballpark, WVU Athletics and West Virginia University are encouraging fans to arrive early ahead of all games in the Morgantown Super Regional.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/3/WVU_V_UK_Monday-12.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/3/WVU_V_UK_Monday-12.jpeg"><media:title>Tailgating at Kendrick Family Ballpark</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/3/WVU_V_UK_Monday-12.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 3 Jun 2026 12:20:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59160</s:story_id></item><item><title>WVU Athletics Names The Goat WV Pub the Official Sports Pub of the Mountaineers</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/2/general-wvu-athletics-names-the-goat-wv-pub-the-official-sports-pub-of-the-mountaineers</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/2/general-wvu-athletics-names-the-goat-wv-pub-the-official-sports-pub-of-the-mountaineers</guid><category>General</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="The GOAT has been Named the Official Sports Pub of WVU Athletics" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/2/WVU_x_The_Goat__3_.png" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W. Va. – West Virginia Athletics and Mountaineer Sports Properties announced today a five-year partnership extension with The Goat WV Pub that includes the creation a new Gold & Blue NIL Show.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/WVU_x_The_Goat__3_.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/WVU_x_The_Goat__3_.png"><media:title>The GOAT has been Named the Official Sports Pub of WVU Athletics</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/WVU_x_The_Goat__3_.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 2 Jun 2026 13:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>3</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59158</s:story_id></item><item><title>Baseball Fans, Savor These Special Moments</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/2/baseball-fans-savor-these-special-moments</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/2/baseball-fans-savor-these-special-moments</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="West Virginia fans celebrate the Mountaineers' walk-off, 6-5 victory over Kentucky in the deciding game of the Morgantown Regional played at Kendrick Family Ballpark on Monday, June 1, 2026." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/2/Celebration-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – I'm old, and watching college baseball games these last couple of days has made me feel much older.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/Celebration-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/Celebration-Main.jpg"><media:title>West Virginia fans celebrate the Mountaineers' walk-off, 6-5 victory over Kentucky in the deciding game of the Morgantown Regional played at Kendrick Family Ballpark on Monday, June 1, 2026.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/Celebration-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 2 Jun 2026 08:58:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59157</s:story_id></item><item><title>Bridgeport’s McDougal Seizes Opportunity to Extend West Virginia’s Season</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/1/baseball-bridgeports-mcdougal-seizes-opportunity-to-extend-west-virginias-season</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/1/baseball-bridgeports-mcdougal-seizes-opportunity-to-extend-west-virginias-season</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="West Virginia players celebrate winning pitcher Ben McDougal's five-inning relief stint in the Mountaineers' 11-9 victory over Kentucky to set up a deciding game five on Monday at Kendrick Family Ballpark in Morgantown, W.Va." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/1/McDougal2-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – During a long, 12-hour day when West Virginia pounded out 23 hits and 21 runs in victories over Wake Forest and Kentucky, you knew for the Mountaineers to keep their postseason hopes alive, somebody in a gold-colored jersey was going to have to man-up on the pitching mound.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/McDougal2-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/McDougal2-Main.jpg"><media:title>West Virginia players celebrate winning pitcher Ben McDougal's five-inning relief stint in the Mountaineers' 11-9 victory over Kentucky to set up a deciding game five on Monday at Kendrick Family Ballpark in Morgantown, W.Va.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/McDougal2-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 1 Jun 2026 00:32:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59153</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Rally to Defeat Kentucky and Force Game Seven</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/1/baseball-mountaineers-rally-to-defeat-kentucky-and-force-game-seven</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/1/baseball-mountaineers-rally-to-defeat-kentucky-and-force-game-seven</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Paul Schoenfeld hits a home run against Kentucky in the NCAA Regional" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/1/WVU_v_WAKE_2026_Sunday_Regional-226.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 16 West Virginia University baseball team scored five runs in the top of the ninth to defeat Kentucky, 11-9, Sunday evening and force a game seven. First pitch against the Wildcats on Monday is set for 6 p.m.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/WVU_v_WAKE_2026_Sunday_Regional-226.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/WVU_v_WAKE_2026_Sunday_Regional-226.jpg"><media:title>Paul Schoenfeld hits a home run against Kentucky in the NCAA Regional</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/WVU_v_WAKE_2026_Sunday_Regional-226.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 1 Jun 2026 00:04:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59152</s:story_id></item><item><title>WVU’s Tavon Austin, Jim Carlen on 2027 NFF College Football Hall of Fame Ballot</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/1/wvus-tavon-austin-jim-carlen-on-2027-nff-college-football-hall-of-fame-ballot</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/1/wvus-tavon-austin-jim-carlen-on-2027-nff-college-football-hall-of-fame-ballot</guid><category>Football</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tavon Austin, scoring one of his four touchdowns against Clemson in the 2012 Discover Orange Bowl, is listed on the ballot for the 2027 College Football Hall of Fame." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/1/Austin-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Electrifying West Virginia University All-American wide receiver Tavon Austin is a first-time designee on the ballot for this year's College Football Hall of Fame released by the National Football Foundation (NFF) earlier today.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/Austin-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/Austin-Main.jpg"><media:title>Tavon Austin, scoring one of his four touchdowns against Clemson in the 2012 Discover Orange Bowl, is listed on the ballot for the 2027 College Football Hall of Fame.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/Austin-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 1 Jun 2026 11:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>2</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59155</s:story_id></item><item><title>Three Mountaineers Advance to NCAA Outdoor Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/30/track-field-three-mountaineers-advance-to-ncaa-outdoor-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/30/track-field-three-mountaineers-advance-to-ncaa-outdoor-championships</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Joy Naukot competing in the 10,000 meters at the NCAA East First Round" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/30/IMG_1354.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University track and field team qualified three student-athletes for the NCAA Outdoor Championships following competition at the NCAA East First Round in Lexington, Kentucky.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/IMG_1354.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/IMG_1354.jpg"><media:title>Joy Naukot competing in the 10,000 meters at the NCAA East First Round</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/IMG_1354.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 23:01:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59150</s:story_id></item><item><title>Duke’s Mayo Classic v. Virginia Ticket Requests Now Available</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/29/football-dukes-mayo-classic-v-virginia-ticket-requests-now-available</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/29/football-dukes-mayo-classic-v-virginia-ticket-requests-now-available</guid><category>Football</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="BankAmericaStadium" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/29/AU4U8549.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Ticket requests for WVU football season ticket holders and Mountaineer Athletic Club (MAC) members are now available for the Duke's Mayo Classic, WVU vs. Virginia, on Sept. 19, at Bank of America Stadium, in Charlotte, North Carolina.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/29/AU4U8549.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/29/AU4U8549.jpg"><media:title>BankAmericaStadium</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/29/AU4U8549.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 10:33:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>2</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59145</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>